'''腦磁波儀'''（{{lang-en|Magnetoencephalography}}，简称'''MEG'''）是一種{{Link-en|功能性神經成像|}}技術，透過非常靈敏的[[磁强计|磁強計]]紀錄[[人腦|大腦]]自然產生的[[电流|電流]]所產生的[[磁場|磁場]]，繪製大腦活動的影像。 [[超導量子干涉儀|超導量子干涉儀]]（superconducting quantum unit interference devices, SQUID）陣列是目前最常見的磁強計，而{{Link-en|無自旋交換鬆弛|}}（spin exchange relaxation-free, SERF ）磁強計則在進行研究，做為未來使用的儀器。<ref name="HämäläinenHari1993">{{Cite journal|title=Magnetoencephalography—theory, instrumentation, and applications to noninvasive studies of the working human brain|url=https://aaltodoc.aalto.fi/bitstream/123456789/18757/1/A1_h%c3%a4m%c3%a4l%c3%a4inen_matti_1993.pdf|last=Hämäläinen|first=Matti|last2=Hari|first2=Riitta|journal=Reviews of Modern Physics|issue=2|doi=10.1103/RevModPhys.65.413|year=1993|volume=65|pages=413–497|format=vanc|bibcode=1993RvMP...65..413H|issn=0034-6861|last3=Ilmoniemi|first3=Risto J.|last4=Knuutila|first4=Jukka|last5=Lounasmaa|first5=Olli V.|access-date=2020-06-30|archive-date=2020-03-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312063223/https://aaltodoc.aalto.fi/bitstream/handle/123456789/18757/A1_h%C3%A4m%C3%A4l%C3%A4inen_matti_1993.pdf;jsessionid=29AB167EFA05F1B2C9D634FABF87C533?sequence=1|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|title=Moving magnetoencephalography towards real-world applications with a wearable system|last=Boto|first=Elena|last2=Holmes|first2=Niall|date=March 2018|journal=Nature|issue=7698|doi=10.1038/nature26147|volume=555|pages=657–661|language=En|bibcode=2018Natur.555..657B|issn=1476-4687|pmc=6063354|pmid=29562238|last3=Leggett|first3=James|last4=Roberts|first4=Gillian|last5=Shah|first5=Vishal|last6=Meyer|first6=Sofie S.|last7=Muñoz|first7=Leonardo Duque|last8=Mullinger|first8=Karen J.|last9=Tierney|first9=Tim M.}}</ref>腦磁波儀包括對知覺和認知MEG的应用包括對知覺和大腦認知過程的基礎研究，和在手術切除前定位受病理影響的區域，确定腦各部位的功能以及{{Internal link helper/en|神經回饋|}}。可以應用於臨床上發現異常的位置，也可以應用於實驗上簡單的量測腦部活動。<ref>{{Cite book|last=Carlson|first=Neil R.|format=vanc|year=2013|title=Physiology of Behavior|url=https://archive.org/details/physiologybehavi00carl_811|location=Upper Saddle River, NJ|publisher=Pearson Education Inc.|isbn=978-0-205-23939-9|pages=[https://archive.org/details/physiologybehavi00carl_811/page/n172 152]–153}}</ref>

